ues are\nconsistent, provided the selection effect against Cepheids with higher values\nof A_I is taken into account. The implications from these relations for disk\nphotometry, M/L conversion and galaxy dynamical modeling are briefly discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 15 Sep 2005 12:16:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-11"}
